OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1775178189
OL,3,CBereaved families welcome launch of
OL,4,Cnational knife crime centre
OL,6,FONS figures show that whilst the last
OL,7,Fyear, up to September 2025, saw a 9%
OL,8,Ffall in reports Police-recorded
OL,9,Foffences involving a knife or sharp
OL,10,Finstrument, incidents have increased
OL,11,Fby 54% when compared with March 2015.
OL,13,FPooja Kanda said the centre's launch
OL,14,Fwas a "bittersweet moment", but that
OL,15,Fwe "must make sure no other child
OL,16,Floses their life like he (her son)
OL,17,Fdid."
OL,26,@xD@ZpmxD@bpn
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
