OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1775178189
OL,3,CBereaved families welcome launch of
OL,4,Cnational knife crime centre
OL,6,FPooja Kanda, whose son Ronan was
OL,7,Ffatally stabbed in 2022 said the
OL,8,Finitiative should be "welcomed with
OL,9,Fboth hands".
OL,11,FShe added: "As a mother who has lost
OL,12,Fher son to knife crime, I know the
OL,13,Fdevastating reality behind the
OL,14,Fstatistics. Ronan was an innocent
OL,15,Fchild, taken in an instant ` and no
OL,16,Ffamily should have to live with that
OL,17,Fpain.
OL,19,F"The launch of the National Knife
OL,20,FCrime Centre is a significant and
OL,21,Fnecessary step forward.
OL,26,@sD@LOU{D@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
